# Deterministic line endings.
#
# The repo previously had no .gitattributes, so files were normalized per each
# machine's `core.autocrlf`. That produced phantom "modified" diffs (LF vs CRLF
# with no content change) whenever a tool wrote a different line ending than Git
# expected. Git always stores LF in the blob; the working-tree endings below are
# explicit so they no longer depend on local config.

# Default: auto-detect text, store as LF, and check out as LF on every platform.
# (Binary files are auto-detected and left untouched; explicit types are below.)
* text=auto eol=lf

# These must check out as CRLF:
#   - Rust, to satisfy rustfmt's `newline_style = "Windows"` (otherwise
#     `cargo fmt --check` fails on LF input);
#   - Windows batch scripts, which can misbehave with LF line endings.
*.rs  text eol=crlf
*.bat text eol=crlf
*.cmd text eol=crlf

# Explicit binary types — never normalized or line-ending converted.
*.ico  binary
*.png  binary
*.jpg  binary
*.jpeg binary
*.gif  binary
*.webp binary
*.gguf binary
*.onnx binary
*.db   binary
*.bin  binary
